The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Calcutta, Sept. 12: IFGL Inc of the US  the 100 per cent owned US subsidiary of IFGL Refractories Ltd  has acquired a 100 per cent interest in EI Ceramics LLC and CUSC International Ltd as going concerns free of long-term debts. These transactions were consummated today, in Cincinnati, Ohio.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 12: Bengal Aerotropolis Projects Ltd will raise Rs 600 crore in the next 8-10 weeks to develop the first phase of the Rs 10,000-crore airport city project at Andal in Bengal by 2012.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 12: The BSE has invited broker-members to register with its wireless platform that will allow investors to place buy or sell orders using mobile phones. The guidelines for wireless trading follows an August 27 circular by Sebi.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 12: Reliance Industries has announced the completion of its deal to acquire a 60 per cent stake in the Marcellus Shale gas asset in the US for $392 million.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 12: India and Japan have reached an in-principle agreement on trade-opening partnership and it is likely to be signed during Prime Minister Manmohan Singhs visit to Tokyo in October.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 12: The parliamentary panel reviewing the companies bill has said the corporate affairs ministry should monitor the end use of money raised by companies through initial public offerings.                                                                                                                          
